qas.question: What types of services will be offered by the BeiDou system?

answers.text: a free service to civilians and licensed service to the Chinese government and military

qas.question: What is the range of accuracy for the free service offered to civilians?
What is the range of accuracy for the licensed service used by Chinese government and military?
As of right now, who uses the licensed military service?

answers.text: the People's Liberation Army and to the Military of Pakistan

qas.question: What is something the licensed military service can be used for?

plausible_answers.text: licensed service to the Chinese government

qas.question: Aside from the charged service to civilians, what is the other level of service provided?
Aside from the licensed service to Japanese civilians, what is the other level of service provided?

plausible_answers.text: 10-meter location-tracking accuracy, synchronizes clocks with an accuracy of 10 nanoseconds, and measures speeds to within 0.2 m/s.

qas.question: The paid civilian service offers which features?
The service licensed to Japanese government has a location accuracy of what?
The paid civilian service has a location tracking accuracy of how many meters?
